'''朝鮮民主主義人民共和國集中營'''，或稱'''強制收容所'''，是[[朝鮮民主主義人民共和國|朝鮮民主主義人民共和國]]境內的一种用于[[刑事拘留|刑事拘留]]和勞役懲罰的場所，主要收容大量[[政治犯|政治犯]]。这些场所在朝鲜没有统一的名称，有“[[管理所|管理所]]”(主要囚禁政治犯、叛国者与反[[金日成家族|金日成家族]]的人，民间称“地獄”）、“教化所”（囚禁罪行较重者）、“勞動鍛煉隊”（囚禁[[脱北者|脱北]]失败者）、“集結所”（囚禁未处决犯人）、“監獄”、“拘留場”、“預防院”（以精神病院為幌子的政治犯拘留所）等不同的叫法。它们的管理機構也不盡相同，大多是朝鲜[[國家保衛省|國家保衛省]]和[[朝鲜民主主义人民共和国人民保安部|人民保安部]]。<ref name="info">[http://www.hrnk.org/hiddengulag/introduction.html U.S. Committee for Human Rights in North Korea] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090612063340/http://www.hrnk.org/hiddengulag/introduction.html |date=2009-06-12 }}</ref>[[國際社會|國際社會]]普遍認為其中存在侵害[[人權|人權]]的行为，包括[[飢餓|飢餓]]、[[酷刑|酷刑]]、[[性侵犯|性侵犯]]、公開和秘密處決、强制劳动等。<ref name="info" /><ref>{{cite web |url=http://discovery.163.com/12/0602/10/8305OH7I000125LI.html?from=index |language= |title=脱北者眼里的北韓集中营 |publisher=网易探索 |date=2012-06-02 |accessdate= |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120605032513/http://discovery.163.com/12/0602/10/8305OH7I000125LI.html?from=index |archivedate=2012年6月5日 |df= }}</ref>其中不少被关押者会被认定“不可救药”，然后服劳役至死<ref>{{cite web |url=http://discovery.163.com/12/0403/11/7U5OS9CR000125LI.html |language= |title=一个脱北者的惊险历程：逃出朝鲜14号劳改营 |publisher=网易探索 |date=2012-04-03 |accessdate= |archive-date=2018-02-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180207032842/http://discovery.163.com/12/0403/11/7U5OS9CR000125LI.html |dead-url=yes }}</ref>。

根据人权团体的调查（如[[国际特赦组织|国际特赦组织]]<ref>{{cite web| title= North Korea: Political Prison Camps| work= Amnesty International, May 3, 2011| url= http://www.amnesty.org/en/library/asset/ASA24/001/2011/en/2671e54f-1cd1-46c1-96f1-6a463efa6f65/asa240012011en.pdf| accessdate= June 6, 2013| archive-date= 2012-03-09| archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20120309142353/http://www.amnesty.org/en/library/asset/ASA24/001/2011/en/2671e54f-1cd1-46c1-96f1-6a463efa6f65/asa240012011en.pdf| dead-url= yes}}</ref>、[[人权观察|人权观察]]<ref>{{cite web | title= World Report 2013 North Korea | work= Human Rights Watch | url= http://www.hrw.org/world-report/2013/country-chapters/north-korea?page=1 | accessdate= June 6, 2013 | archive-date= 2021-03-05 | archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20210305044806/https://www.hrw.org/world-report/2013/country-chapters/north-korea?page=1 | dead-url= no }}</ref>和[[联合国人权事务高级专员|联合国人权事务高级专员]]<ref>{{cite web| title= Pillay urges more attention to human rights abuses in North Korea, calls for international inquiry| work= United Nations Office of the High Commissioner for Human Rights, January 14, 2013| url= http://www.ohchr.org/en/NewsEvents/Pages/DisplayNews.aspx?NewsID=12923&LangID=E| accessdate= June 6, 2013| archive-date= 2013-02-09| archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20130209173351/http://www.ohchr.org/EN/NewsEvents/Pages/DisplayNews.aspx?NewsID=12923&LangID=E| dead-url= no}}</ref>），北韓监狱里的条件非常恶劣，犯人的生命岌岌可危。<ref>{{cite web| title=2009 Human Rights Report: Democratic People's Republic of Korea| work=U.S. Department of State| url=http://www.state.gov/g/drl/rls/hrrpt/2009/eap/135995.htm| accessdate=May 4, 2010| archive-date=2012-01-13| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120113102742/http://www.state.gov/g/drl/rls/hrrpt/2009/eap/135995.htm| dead-url=no}}</ref>他们还会受到[[酷刑|酷刑]]及其他非人道的待遇。<ref>{{cite web| title=North Korea: Torture, death penalty and abductions| work=Amnesty International| url=http://www.amnesty.org/en/library/info/ASA24/003/2009/en| accessdate=May 4, 2010| archive-date=2014-10-31| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141031235428/http://www.amnesty.org/en/library/info/ASA24/003/2009/en| dead-url=no}}</ref>公开和秘密处决犯人（包括儿童）——特别是涉及到试图逃出国外的人时，是家常便饭。<ref>{{cite web| title=White paper on human rights in North Korea 2009 (page 74–75)| work=Korea Institute for National Unification| url=http://www.kinu.or.kr/2009/0727/white2009_e.pdf| accessdate=May 4, 2010| archive-date=2016-03-08| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160308064925/http://kinu.or.kr/2009/0727/white2009_e.pdf| dead-url=no}}</ref>[[杀婴|杀婴]]行为（包括强制[[堕胎|堕胎]]和杀害新生儿<ref>{{cite web| title=The Hidden Gulag – Part Three: Summary of torture and infanticide information (page 70–72)| work=The Committee for Human Rights in North Korea| url=http://hrnk.org/wp-content/uploads/The_Hidden_Gulag.pdf| accessdate=November 11, 2010| archive-date=2011-12-21| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111221084418/http://hrnk.org/wp-content/uploads/The_Hidden_Gulag.pdf| dead-url=yes}}</ref>）也时常发生。监狱中犯人的[[死亡率|死亡率]]一直居高不下，常见的死因有饥饿<ref>{{cite news | title=Running Out of the Darkness | work=TIME Magazine | url=http://www.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,1186569,00.html | accessdate=October 31, 2006 | date=April 24, 2006 | archive-date=2011-08-20 | archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/614VAM5Ho?url=http://www.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,1186569,00.html | dead-url=yes }}</ref>、疾病<ref>{{cite news | title=N. Korean Defectors Describe Brutal Abuse | work=The [[Associated_Press|Associated Press]] | url=http://www.cbsnews.com/stories/2008/10/29/world/main4555614.shtml?source=RSSattr=World_4555614 | accessdate=December 16, 2008 | date=October 29, 2008 | archive-date=2009-05-15 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090515144943/http://www.cbsnews.com/stories/2008/10/29/world/main4555614.shtml?source=RSSattr=World_4555614 | dead-url=yes }}</ref>、劳动事故和酷刑等。北韓政府否认所有人权团体的指控，声称酷刑虐待犯人是该国刑事诉讼法所不容许的<ref>{{cite web | title=Report of the Working Group on the Universal Periodic Review: Democratic People’s Republic of Korea (page 7) | work=United Nations Human Rights Council | url=http://lib.ohchr.org/HRBodies/UPR/Documents/Session6/KP/A_HRC_13_13_PRK_E.pdf | accessdate=May 11, 2010 | archive-date=2011-07-21 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110721182559/http://lib.ohchr.org/HRBodies/UPR/Documents/Session6/KP/A_HRC_13_13_PRK_E.pdf | dead-url=no }}</ref>。但前囚犯的证言表明，北韓政府的言行完全不一致。<ref>{{cite web | title=Submission to the UN Universal Periodic Review on the Democratic People’s Republic of Korea (page 8) | work=Citizens’ Alliance for North Korean Human Rights (NKHR) and Korean Bar Association (KBA) | url=http://lib.ohchr.org/HRBodies/UPR/Documents/Session6/KP/NKHR-KBA_UPR_S06_2009.pdf | accessdate=May 11, 2010 | archive-date=2011-07-21 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110721182315/http://lib.ohchr.org/HRBodies/UPR/Documents/Session6/KP/NKHR-KBA_UPR_S06_2009.pdf | dead-url=no }}</ref>北韓政府不仅拒绝提供集中營内犯人的信息，而且不允许任何人权团体进入集中营内部考察。<ref>{{cite web | title=Report by the Special Rapporteur on Torture and Other Cruel, Inhuman, or Degrading Treatment or Punishment, Theo van Boven: Democratic People’s Republic of Korea | work=United Nations/Derechos Human Rights | url=http://derechos.org/nizkor/torture/vanboven/prk.html | accessdate=May 11, 2010 | archive-date=2008-09-06 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080906121240/http://www.derechos.org/nizkor/torture/vanboven/prk.html | dead-url=no }}</ref>

在20世纪50年代，[[旅日朝鲜人总联合会|旅-{日朝}-鲜人总联合会]]呼吁朝-{}-鲜人返回“社会主义人间天堂”、地上樂園北朝鲜居住。此举被[[在日本大韩民国民团|民团]]强烈反对。大约有87000名在日朝鲜人和6000多日本配偶返回了朝鲜。日本有调查显示，在返回的人中，有大约1万人被送入监狱或集中營。<ref>{{cite news |title=Spy's escape from North Korean 'hell' |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/asia-pacific/2631839.stm |accessdate=2020-08-03 |agency=BBC |date=2003-01-06 |archive-date=2020-08-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200806044109/http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/asia-pacific/2631839.stm |dead-url=no }}</ref>

2002年，[[李顺玉|李顺玉]]在[[美国众议院|美国众议院]]给出证词，详细的描述了她在北韓集中營内的生活。她说：“我可以作证，1987年我被送进监狱时已关在里面的6000名犯人，到了我1992年出狱时，大部分都因为环境恶劣而悄无声息地死去了。”<ref name="judiciary.senate.gov">{{cite web| title=Testimony of Ms. Soon Ok Lee, North Korean prison camp survivor| work=United States Senate Hearings| url=http://judiciary.senate.gov/hearings/testimony.cfm?id=292&wit_id=665| accessdate=November 11, 2010| archive-date=2008-09-22| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080922033340/http://judiciary.senate.gov/hearings/testimony.cfm?id=292&wit_id=665| dead-url=no}}</ref>其他一些犯人，如[[姜哲焕|姜哲焕]]和人权活动者[[申东赫|申东赫]]，也给出了与此相符的有关集中营是如何危害人权的证词。

根据前监狱营看守[[安明哲|安明哲]]的证词，守卫会受“把拘押者当成次等人类”的专门训练，他还提到了一个集中营里的小孩，只为了争夺一根从牛槽里捡来的玉米核而打架的事。<ref>National Geographic: Inside North Korea, aired on the History Channel in 2006, accessed on Netflix July 22, 2011</ref>

北韓的关押营可分为大型的政治犯关押营（朝语：관리소，意为管理所）和劳改营（朝语：교화소，意为教化所）两种<ref>{{cite web| title=The Hidden Gulag – Part Three: Kwan-li-so political panel-labor colonies (page 24 - 41), Kyo-hwa-so prison-labor facilities (page 41 - 55)| work=The Committee for Human Rights in North Korea| url=http://hrnk.org/wp-content/uploads/The_Hidden_Gulag.pdf| accessdate=November 11, 2010| archive-date=2011-12-21| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111221084418/http://hrnk.org/wp-content/uploads/The_Hidden_Gulag.pdf| dead-url=yes}}</ref>。管理所内又分為革命化区域和完全統制区域，前者可通過领导人特赦（如[[太阳节|金日成生日]]、[[光明星节|金正日生日]]）等原因获释，后者属終身監禁，無任何获释可能。

而營方為鼓勵勞動，有時會批准非政治犯罪的男女囚犯結婚，每半個月相見一次。


